{"title":"Here’s what it takes to Everest on a bike  (8,880m in under 15 hours!)","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/08/03/heres-what-it-takes-to-everest-on-a-bike-8880m-in-under-15-hours/","date":1627992668000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p>Italian Gabriele Boasso recently completed an Everesting challenge, climbing 8,800m (28,900 feet) in just under 15 hours of ride time. Here’s how he did it, what it felt like, his bike spec, and what he ate and drank during the ride…</p><h3>What it felt like Everesting on a bike</h3><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073729/gabriele-boassa-everesting-on-bicycle-2021.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073729/gabriele-boassa-everesting-on-bicycle-2021.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:484x308/rscb28/ng:webp/ngcb28\" alt=\"gabriele boassa riding his bike during everesting challenge\" width=\"681\" height=\"434\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073729/gabriele-boassa-everesting-on-bicycle-2021.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 681w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073729/gabriele-boassa-everesting-on-bicycle-2021-297x189.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073729/gabriele-boassa-everesting-on-bicycle-2021-120x76.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073729/gabriele-boassa-everesting-on-bicycle-2021-659x420.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 659w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 681px) 100vw, 681px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073729/gabriele-boassa-everesting-on-bicycle-2021.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:484x308/rscb28/ng:webp/ngcb28\" ezoid=\"0.3030136670164285\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073729/gabriele-boassa-everesting-on-bicycle-2021.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 681w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073729/gabriele-boassa-everesting-on-bicycle-2021-297x189.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073729/gabriele-boassa-everesting-on-bicycle-2021-120x76.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073729/gabriele-boassa-everesting-on-bicycle-2021-659x420.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 659w\"></a></p><p>Starting at 5am, Gabriele rode a total of 270.9 kilometers, riding an uphill segment of Gorra-Cà del Din (on the Melogno hill, just inland of Finale Ligure, Italy. That totaled 8,880m of climbing over 12.5 laps up and down the hill. Check out <a href=\"https://www.strava.com/activities/5534036746\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">the ride on Strava here</a>. And check out the <a href=\"https://www.strava.com/segments/665983\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Gorra-Colle del Melogno Strava Segment</a> if you’re ever in the area.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03071743/strava-profile-everesting-on-a-bike.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03071743/strava-profile-everesting-on-a-bike.jpg\" alt=\"strava ride profile of everesting on a bike\" width=\"1208\" height=\"526\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03071743/strava-profile-everesting-on-a-bike.jpg 1208w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03071743/strava-profile-everesting-on-a-bike-297x129.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03071743/strava-profile-everesting-on-a-bike-800x348.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03071743/strava-profile-everesting-on-a-bike-120x52.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03071743/strava-profile-everesting-on-a-bike-768x334.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03071743/strava-profile-everesting-on-a-bike-696x303.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03071743/strava-profile-everesting-on-a-bike-1068x465.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03071743/strava-profile-everesting-on-a-bike-965x420.jpg 965w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1208px) 100vw, 1208px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03071743/strava-profile-everesting-on-a-bike.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03071743/strava-profile-everesting-on-a-bike.jpg 1208w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03071743/strava-profile-everesting-on-a-bike-297x129.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03071743/strava-profile-everesting-on-a-bike-800x348.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03071743/strava-profile-everesting-on-a-bike-120x52.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03071743/strava-profile-everesting-on-a-bike-768x334.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03071743/strava-profile-everesting-on-a-bike-696x303.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03071743/strava-profile-everesting-on-a-bike-1068x465.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03071743/strava-profile-everesting-on-a-bike-965x420.jpg 965w\"></a></p><p>Technically, all he needed was 8,848m of climbing to officially count <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Everesting\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">as an Everesting attempt</a>, which would match the height of Mount Everest, first climbed on a bike by George Mallory (grandson of the George Mallory who died on Everest).</p><p>Boasso’s&nbsp;attempt took 14h 44m 45s of ride time, with a total attempt time of 16h 5m including rest and food stops. The record is just under 9 hours for women, and 6h 40m for men, in case you want to give it a go.</p><p>He told us the hardest part was the last 3km of each ascent, which had an average 9% grade. Boasso says after about 6000m of climbing, it’s just a head game. And after 7000m, he felt like he could have picked up the pace, but kept it steady rather than risk blowing up. Other than a few moments of stomach distress, he says it was a great experience (and that we should all try it!).</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073700/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073700/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-2.jpg\" alt=\"gabriele boassa everesting bike build details\" width=\"1200\" height=\"900\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073700/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-2.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073700/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-2-297x223.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073700/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-2-800x600.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073700/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-2-120x90.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073700/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-2-768x576.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073700/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-2-696x522.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073700/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-2-1068x801.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073700/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-2-560x420.jpg 560w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073700/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-2-80x60.jpg 80w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073700/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-2-265x198.jpg 265w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073700/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-2.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073700/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-2.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073700/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-2-297x223.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073700/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-2-800x600.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073700/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-2-120x90.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073700/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-2-768x576.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073700/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-2-696x522.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073700/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-2-1068x801.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073700/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-2-560x420.jpg 560w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073700/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-2-80x60.jpg 80w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073700/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-2-265x198.jpg 265w\"></a></p><h3>Training for an Everesting ride</h3><p>He told us his workouts were similar to those done to prepare for a Marathon season in MTB. That meant 6 workouts a week with 1 day of rest, which included strength training twice a week and one long-distance training ride.</p><p>Total training time was 12-14 hours per week on average.&nbsp;In the last 4 weeks before Everesting, he said it’s best to do 3000m at least once, then 4000m the next time, and log at least one 7-hour ride.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073654/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073654/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-1.jpg\" alt=\"gabriele boassa everesting bike build details\" width=\"1600\" height=\"686\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073654/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-1.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073654/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-1-297x127.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073654/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-1-800x343.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073654/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-1-120x51.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073654/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-1-768x329.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073654/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-1-1536x659.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073654/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-1-696x298.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073654/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-1-1068x458.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073654/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-1-980x420.jpg 980w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073654/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-1.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073654/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-1.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073654/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-1-297x127.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073654/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-1-800x343.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073654/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-1-120x51.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073654/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-1-768x329.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073654/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-1-1536x659.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073654/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-1-696x298.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073654/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-1-1068x458.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073654/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-1-980x420.jpg 980w\"></a></p><h3>The Everesting bike setup</h3><p>Gabriele rode his Canyon Endurace, a bike we’ve reviewed and really liked for long distance cruising. It’s light on its own, and while Gabriele’s bike build is no slouch, you’ll notice that there’s nothing exceptionally boutique or crazy light about the parts. Here’s the complete build spec:</p><ul><li>Canyon Endurace Cf SLX</li><li>Reynolds Assault LE 50mm wheels</li><li>Ultegra R8000 group</li><li>52/36 crankset</li><li>Cassette 11/28</li><li><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021/07/23/favero-assioma-duo-shi-puts-power-meters-inside-your-shimano-spd-sl-road-pedals/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Favero Assioma Duo</a> power meter pedals</li><li>Continental GP5000 TLR tire</li><li>San Marco X-LR saddle</li><li>Garmin Edge 520 + HR chest strap</li></ul><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073712/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-4.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073712/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-4.jpg\" alt=\"gabriele boassa everesting bike build details\" width=\"1200\" height=\"900\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073712/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-4.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073712/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-4-297x223.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073712/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-4-800x600.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073712/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-4-120x90.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073712/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-4-768x576.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073712/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-4-696x522.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/03073712/gabriele-boassa-everesting-bike-build-spec-4-106